g.text: OpenHDS Tablet provides the main entrypoint for admins
and data collectors (field workers). It uses data loaded by
an admin (supervisor) to authenticate field workers and
to drive the location hierarchy-based form management.
ODK Collect is used to handle all of the actual data entry.
Form definitions are fetched from ODK Aggregate prior to
running OpenHDS Tablet, and when a user selects a form
in the Tablet application, the appropriate form definition
is selected and populated with seed data via an Intent
configured by Tablet to launch the Collect activity.
Collect handles the form entry, possibly launching other
activities based on the form definitions, such as entering
Saved forms are returned to the Tablet application via
Intent. They are encrypted and stored in Tablet and
Form submission is initiated through the admin interface
in Tablet, which decrypts the stored forms and launches
an upload Activity in Collect via Intent. If successful,
Collect submits forms to Aggregate and when control is
sent back to Tablet it finds no forms to encrypt.
ODK Aggregate is responsible for serving and handling form submissions from Collect.
Mirth is responsible for integrating Aggregate and OpenHDS by transferring information
submitted as forms to Aggregate to corresponding REST endpoints exposed by OpenHDS.
The 'Census Events' channel defines a job that polls a fixed number of ODK tables for new
records, marks them as 'handled', converts them to XML and posts them to the
an OpenHDS endpoint corresponding to the form.
OpenHDS is primarily responsible for handling XML submissions from mirth corresponding
to the various forms, providing data synchronization endpoints for populating the tablet app
